## Git Workflow

<!-- infer in priority order: CONTRIBUTING.md, then .github/, then commit history -->

### Branch Names

`[feature/bugfix/hotfix]/[ticket-id]-[short-description]`

Examples: `feature/ABC-123-add-user-auth`, `bugfix/fix-login-redirect`

### Commit Messages

`[type]([scope]): [description]`

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`. Body optional.

### PR Checklist

- [ ] Lint passes
- [ ] Tests pass
- [ ] [Detect — extra gates from CI or contribution docs]

> Downstream commit/MR tooling reads git conventions from the git-workflow standards
> guide; keep this section consistent with it.

